{
  "info": {
    "name": "mpt-extension-sdk mock_app",
    "description": "Sample requests for the SDK mock_app running locally on `{{base_url}}` (default `http://localhost:8080`).\n\nAuth is wired automatically:\n\n- A collection-level pre-request script builds a non-prod HS256 JWT from the `extension_id`, `account_id` and `account_type` variables and stores it in `auth_token`.\n- Every authenticated request sends `Authorization: Bearer {{auth_token}}` via collection-level Bearer auth (the `ops` requests opt out).\n\nThe runtime (mpt-extension-sdk) decodes claims without verifying the signature, so the HS256 dummy secret is only there to produce a structurally valid token. Override `extension_id`, `account_id` or `account_type` in the collection variables to test other identities.",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "auth": {
    "type": "bearer",
    "bearer": [
      {
        "key": "token",
        "value": "{{auth_token}}",
        "type": "string"
      }
    ]
  },
  "event": [
    {
      "listen": "prerequest",
      "script": {
        "type": "text/javascript",
        "exec": [
          "// Build a non-prod HS256 JWT for the local runtime and store it in `auth_token`.",
          "// The runtime decodes claims without verifying the signature, so the dummy",
          "// secret below is fine for local testing only.",
          "const CryptoJS = require('crypto-js');",
          "",
          "const b64url = (wordArray) => CryptoJS.enc.Base64.stringify(wordArray)",
          "    .replace(/=+$/, '').replace(/\\+/g, '-').replace(/\\//g, '_');",
          "const b64urlStr = (s) => b64url(CryptoJS.enc.Utf8.parse(s));",
          "",
          "const header = b64urlStr(JSON.stringify({ alg: 'HS256', typ: 'JWT' }));",
          "const payload = b64urlStr(JSON.stringify({",
          "    'https://claims.softwareone.com/extensionId': pm.collectionVariables.get('extension_id'),",
          "    'https://claims.softwareone.com/accountId': pm.collectionVariables.get('account_id'),",
          "    'https://claims.softwareone.com/accountType': pm.collectionVariables.get('account_type'),",
          "    exp: Math.floor(Date.now() / 1000) + 10 * 365 * 24 * 60 * 60",
          "}));",
          "const signature = b64url(CryptoJS.HmacSHA256(header + '.' + payload, 'non-prod-dummy-secret'));",
          "",
          "pm.collectionVariables.set('auth_token', header + '.' + payload + '.' + signature);"
        ]
      }
    }
  ],
  "variable": [
    {
      "key": "base_url",
      "value": "http://localhost:8080",
      "type": "string"
    },
    {
      "key": "extension_id",
      "value": "EXT-2345-3554",
      "type": "string"
    },
    {
      "key": "account_id",
      "value": "ACC-0000-3453",
      "type": "string"
    },
    {
      "key": "account_type",
      "value": "Client",
      "type": "string"
    },
    {
      "key": "auth_token",
      "value": "",
      "type": "string"
    }
  ],
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "ops / health",
      "request": {
        "method": "GET",
        "auth": {
          "type": "noauth"
        },
        "header": [],
        "url": {
          "raw": "{{base_url}}/bypass/health",
          "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
          "path": ["bypass", "health"]
        }
      },
      "response": []
    },
    {
      "name": "ops / live — liveness probe (expected 200 OK)",
      "request": {
